; npm install hardening — viewer project
; Following lirantal/npm-security-best-practices.
;
; engine-strict     Enforce the `engines.node` field instead of warning, so
;                   `npm install` refuses to run on the wrong Node major.
;
; audit-level=high  Make `npm audit` (and the implicit audit during install)
;                   exit non-zero on high or critical advisories. CI also runs
;                   `npm audit --audit-level=high` explicitly.
;
; before=<YYYY-MM-DD>
;                   Quarantine: refuse to install package versions published
;                   after this date. Defense against fresh supply-chain
;                   attacks (e.g. Mini Shai-Hulud, 2026-05-12) where the
;                   malicious version is yanked within hours but anyone who
;                   resolved in the window is compromised.
;
;                   We'd prefer `min-release-age=7` (a rolling cooldown that
;                   doesn't decay), but as of npm 11.11.0 the two configs
;                   are marked `exclusive` and `npm ci` refuses to run when
;                   both are set. The `min-release-age` setting is also
;                   defined-but-not-yet-wired into resolution — only
;                   `before=` actually filters today. Roll the date forward
;                   when you intentionally want to pull newer packages.
;                   Flip to `min-release-age=7` once npm completes the
;                   wiring (likely 11.12+).
;
;                   `npm ci` against a pinned lockfile is unaffected — these
;                   settings only gate fresh resolution.

engine-strict=true
audit-level=high
before=2026-05-06
